Author: prasetya_23
Content:
Fishing for air

I'm fishing for air
Yes the air with the froth of water vapour from evaporating sweat
In the hot sun

Am I crazy to be fishing for air?
Am I crazy to make the beach and the sea now mere concretes?
I'm not crazy

I just want to have a voice in my complaints and rants
Fishing the air became my medium
A metaphor of how can a fisherman who sails the seas and oceans now be hindered by those concretes?

An irony that resonates
From the beads of sweat
Of my labour in the drama of netting the air
Capturing the void
In concrete that is rigid and unfriendly

Author: prasetya_23
Content:
Mother of the sea

A melodious hymn of the crashing waves
Shining in the soft sun like a warm blanket

The embrace of the waves that depart and then come again like a mother lulling a baby to sleep
Connected from the DNA that comes from the womb of the sea and ocean

Meeting the land that calls to my instincts
As a human child with the sea
Like a child who comes into a mother's arms
I don't know what it is that calls as I am drawn
By the blue of the sea and its soothing lapping

Similar to how a mother who is present and calms all the anxiety that hit me

Although the sea that I now visit is not getting better and many are now blocked by concrete, and stakes

Am I wrong if the sea is like a mother? 
But why do humans always hurt and pollute it?

How can I go home? 
How can a human like me feel like I'm back wherever I go?
When even the sea is now wounded and lost

Author: able98able98
Content:
aight, soz cuz this gon' be a bit long
In light of the current debaucle that is our (once) beloved country Indonesia, I was thinking about an Indonesian rendering of Les Miserables' "Do You Hear the People Sing?". I find the title to be very apt considering the deafness of our politicians, their cronies, and the law-enforcement force (both brown and green). And it is a very popular protest song. They used it in Hong Kong, , The Philippines, and most recently in South Korea when their president did an oopsie and the whole country got mad. So an Indonesian version would seem very fitting in this climate

Now while I do have some background in music, I am pretty limited in other forms of capabilities. So here I am thinking if there are any people in this server is, or know someone who might be fitting, maybe a background in music production, composing, choir, instruments and the creative side like video production and post-production, I am up for some talks and discussion because I feel like this could be a rallying cry to possibly unite the people.

A big ask, I know, and even I still dont have any concrete idea of how it'll work and the logistics and stuff. But I hope this could light the idea, a spark or impetus dare I say, of us as a nation achieving something grander. If, pardon, some tiktok dance and brainrot song can convince nearly 58% of the population to do something a certain way, then why not try this one, or at least give it a thought and entertain the idea for a bit

Sorry for long post. Cheers

Passion and obsession‚Ä¶ they start as the same fire, don‚Äôt they? A spark, a warmth, something that makes you feel alive. But somewhere along the way, passion slips from your grasp, and before you know it, obsession has its claws in you. It doesn‚Äôt inspire anymore‚Äîit haunts. It whispers in the back of your mind, turns every thought into a loop you can‚Äôt escape. You tell yourself it‚Äôs still passion, that you‚Äôre still in control, but deep down, you know the truth. Passion fuels, obsession devours. And once the fire has taken everything, what‚Äôs left of you?

Here's Jett from the School of the Cat

Joon Hee (Jett), a half-elf, was despised by her father, who saw her as a mistake. She was sold at a young age to the mages of Stygga Castle, who roam the Maribor borders. Then she was trained in the early Cat School to become a witcher around the 12th century. Joon Hee was mistaken for a boy by other cat-school witchers because she acts and behaves like one. When it was discovered that she was a girl, Master Witcher Gezras prepared a special mutagen because Joon Hee would likely die in the Trial of the Grass since she is a female, and females tend to fail in this trial since certain mutagens are deadly. After the trial, Joon Hee proved to be an excellent witcher, beating all odds about female witchers. She is quick and agile, and she has the ability to deliver powerful strikes. As a result, Master Gezras grants her the diagram of Princess Xinthia's sword, which she would use in many of her adventures on the path. Unfortunately, after Stygga Castle is abandoned due to a never-ending siege from Nilfgaardians, Joon Hee is nowhere to be found. Rumors have it that she fled and followed Gezras along with the Dyn Marv Caravan. However, this is not entirely true, whether she followed Gezras or made her own path. Her absence was unknown until now.....

Content:
Maaf?

Kata yang ku pertanyaan
Apa esensi maaf dan kenapa kita harus memaafkan

Aku bukan pendendam ulung
Tapi aku perlahan sudah malas menerima maaf atau memberi maaf
Kadang kulihat hanya sebuah seremoni yang di ulang
Atau hanya sebagai ekspresi penyesalan

Gestur nya saja hanya kuingat sebagai tanda lebaran bergema
Apakah aku pantas dimaafkan
Atau apakah mereka pantas aku maafkan

Aku bertanya pada diriku kepada tuhan maupun dirinya yang ku bisikan
Apakah aku rela memaafkan seseorang yang kadang saja tak tahu apa salah mereka? 
Apakah aku rela pula dimaafkan tapi kadang egoku saja meminta untuk menang bukan menerima? 

Kadang aku bingung apa itu maaf dan apa itu memaafkan 
Apakah sejenak dunia berubah 

Apakah dunia akan lebih indah 
Atau malah aku sama saja ditipu lagi dan lagi 
Dan aku pun menipu mereka dengan janji janji manis 

Tuk tak mengulangi lagi segala yang menyayat hati 
Melukai diriku dan dia yang ada di ujung sana 

Tak bertemu 
Enggan memulai
Kata maaf 
Lalu menerimanya

It's nice to talk. 
Watching the birds go and flock .

All the thing you've done is but a Prologue.

Do be still, look, and gaze. 
Look, at the small. 
Don't be mournful of your life, be grateful for its days.
Nothing yet colors your hall. 

Stand and ready to defy your sorrow. 
Be safe, friend. Don't you dare go hollow.

Author: unknownblue
Content:
A perfect doll
her smile greased and practiced
her eyes glistened and shined
as the gears on her head spun and twist
for the perfect girl everyone wished

Oil on her veins 
batteries for her heart
even in pain, all she needs is rest
she kept telling herself, close her eyes its just another part
of a role, her perfect self has to play a part

But little does everyone see
her lenses cracked and her lips dry
the smile everyone love is not seen on her eye
She was never a doll everyone make her to be

Behind the smooth mask
lay a girl no one asked
no oil on her veins
only tears and pain

The doll everyone see
was never meant to be
when will the machine break
only for the girls sake

even she doesn't realize
her engine of affection runs dry on self love
forced to work without fuel
she consumes her love even if fake

 Gold of wheat and green of grass mix but not blend, with ocean blue reflecting the sky of man.

Author: the_second_morgan
Content:
**A gibberish from a frozed man.**

*'hot coffee.
there, behind the silhouette.
my eyes are fixed onto the decoration
ive never seen a more stark ceramic than this
clean and no blots to make itself ugly.
its just glass.
the weather has tears
dropping so smoothly down on my lawn
the table has turned to smoke,
my coffee laid bare.
theres a cat now pooping on my lawn
an animal so little, has cousins so big
razor sharp fangs
why cant a fur-filled cat as big as its mane
exists on my front lawn?

sunny days.
the clouds have smiled
the tears have left it dry
to bring new its gleaming glamour.
i lost all taste on men, women, child
animal, object, drink, food, god
subject, words, sentence, punctuates
night and day.
tell me
why am i so tasteless?
eyes looking down to you
blue irises
as blue as violets glancing down
a wall with the white so pure as glass
yet so troubled, fragile, cracked
i ask
do you speak?

it said yes
it craves nothingness.
long i knew he has lost his own taste
same as i do
same as everyone
they never sleep in life
life lets them wake up
the wall is their end.
pure death, white.
mayhaps they are blind
but i am not
because the wall speaks to me."

Author: .ayab
Content:
I wish to die for a cause, dying in a hill with applause. As men fight with no remorse, please judge me not to that which others speak of, but that which i have done.

Its so tiring to live, as mounting failures gnaws and scream with such tremor; that it shakes your soul. An empty soul wonders at a yonder land, as cur he thinks himself. Must i try to walk upon this desolate hill, with no way for me to look down and up, mist that covers my vision, with no future step in sight.

Save‚Äìsave me from such pain and toment as my life went down with nothing to recover. A hole i want to say exist but a hole already filled with such hatred that none can replace.

A look a upon a mirror and rage was all that seen, pathetic as i am. I wish to find hope.

Author: .ayab
Content:
I wish too look upon that peak, so dazziling with gold, so warm with love, as i walk‚Äî**WALK!!!** as i crawl and  **CRAWL!!!**, an effort not repaid but a betrayal that answers, so hurtful that tears can not decribe, i have given everything that i have and noNe of my dreams come true.

Must I continue this? Must i continue this torture, an act of strenght that I do not have nor i can endure. They smile, painful smile that can not be repaid, a debt towards whom i love, a promise that i could not keep, an honor i could not fight for.

Look upon me and you see nothing, look upon me and youll see a fool making a monument of his faiure

Puisi buat emak emak

In my greatest nightmare stood my mother
on a beautiful meadow filled with flowers
Crowns and jewelries adorned her hair
happiness covering her face
Her clothes lacked the usual wear and tear
She stood glimmering in a beautiful dress
Made with great care

In that dream
It was just her and my father
i was not there.

But in her sweetest dreams
There she stood
Crowning my head and body with jewelries
Her Face covered in the brightest smile

She said nothing of the weight
Of the silk stitched with silence
Of the rings that tightened with every praise
Of the meadow where no roots took hold
Only petals that whispers
her struggles

So I woke up‚ÄîAnd I wept.

Black, horned, and slender, with membraneous wings,
They come in legions on the north wind‚Äôs swell
With obscene clutch that titillates and stings,

Author: .ayab
Content:
Grammar di perbaiki

A Field of Defiance

A flower field left unattended,
Yet bloom they did, proud and splendid.
Growing might not depended,
Graceful with the breeze of wind as life intended.

A flower field picked with cruelty,
Seeing their beauty as futility.
No remorse with unkind totality,
Satisfied with life's inequality.

Damnation towards those who are so brutal!
Damnation towards those who make it cruel, all!!
A beauty destroyed with no meaning, 
Ignoring the painful shriek of their screaming?!

How cruel could they be, seeing them as possessions,
How vandals are they? Do they not see their transgressions?
For they do not understand the price of their taking,
A world of power and freedom they are forsaking.

Yet as men walk unbothered,
The field of flowers grows unfettered.
Their strength is never-ending,
Even when lives bend them, they remain unbending.

Author: .ayab
Content:
@constant 

Draft

For him, life is just a never-ending set of unfortunate dominoes‚Äìeach fall even harder than the last. 

There‚Äôs so much that alcohol can do to numb the pain for it all to come back and bite him, his life work in tatters, all the things he fought for now lie in ruin, celebrated by his enemies. 

The promised revolution, a glory they dreamed of, where justice would prevail for all and not the few, that distant dream he shared with his comrades, dashed away for nothing. All that they fought for is for naught; his loved one faces still haunts him; their smiles judging without knowing, a burden he must carry as the last of his kind, of those who held the torch of such an idea, a beautiful notion filled with idealism.
That every man can have bread on their table.

Every woman living out in freedom. 
Every child lives a life without worry.
How distant those things are now,
How painful for him to remember.

Now, there he sat, a Makarov pistol in hand, one bullet left with his name written on it,  surrounded by a sea of flame that he ignores the burns.

Staring at a photo they all took when hope was high and their goal seemed so close, they all tried to look serious, yet he couldn't help but smile, remembering the stories behind it, how stupid now he thinks about it.
 The laughter still echoed in his mind even as its edges started to burn away. 

Chuckling one last time, gazing down at his hand to see the instrument of his end, tear pouring out, yet,  he cant help to be satisfied, no matter how painful his failure is, he is satisfied, his torment about to end, and in that moment he understands why some would believe in God.

 ‚ÄúIf you‚Äôre here,‚Äù he whispers, ‚Äùor even exist, at least grant me this wish. Let me see them once more. Just once more, let me apologize to all of them.  That is at least you can do‚Ä¶.after all you have done.‚Äù
Closing his eyes, swallowing the barrel.
He hesitated, and then it all went black

Author: noathalier
Content:
Title: On a Cobble Street, at Dusk

The street exhales of old rain.
A man stands long beneath a lamp,
an olive coat darkened by work and years,
spent bargaining with necessity.

A worn hat remembers other evenings.
Thirty years, give or take.
His face is folded by a question
he no longer asks aloud.

He studies a poster, how it grins!
selling futures in bright ink
to a soul already bankrupt.
He reads it as one reads scripture
after belief has thinned:
with habit,
with irony,
with a longing he will not confess.

Work has let him go.
So has most else.

He spreads his arms‚Äî
an odd thing to do,
but there‚Äôs no one watching.
The wind licks his palms;
the dying sun stains his mouth
with cigarette and beer.

That will have to be enough.

He is drunk‚Äî
not with joy,
but with the bitter perfume of being alive,
that narcotic which keeps us breathing
long after our dreams have soured.

Beneath his eyes,
two bruises time forgot to heal.
His back bends,
as if carrying a coffin
no one else can see.

Perhaps there was someone once.
Perhaps not.

Either way,
the street keeps its distance.
The evening continues.
Nothing waits
that hasn‚Äôt already learned,
how to be without him.

Perhaps he returns home
to an absence still warm,
to a ghost that sleeps beside him‚Äî
faithful, unfaithful, eternal‚Äî
the only companion
who never leaves.

Author: noathalier
Content:
Title: Pilgrimage 

Shrouded sky,
Rumbling clouds.
Gentle rain,
Chilly wind.

Invigorated forest.
Wet soil.
Brisk leaves.
Crisp branch.

Solemn shrine.
Red altar.
Tranquil candle.
Yellow offering.

Bell's toll.
Morning prayer.
Chanting dharma.
Upon halls of oak and pine, irradiated by candle glow.

Commemorating the departure of a thousand illuminated lords.
